spans.text: Conceptions both of Men and Things
So lately honoured with so much Applause
what Rakes would blush to name
what's rational as well as New
what's rational as well as New
what was Irksome once Delighted most
Sing his Sally's Praise , Though rude the Numbers , yet the Subject moved
in Detraction's Spite Displayed me in a more conspicuous Light
more would prove a needless Task , Why should they not be mine
a needless Task , Why should they not be mine
What I am to do , You'll think
my present Peace , my future Fame
